.\" Man page for perf-tests.sh
.TH PERF-TESTS 1 "2025" "RustOwl" "RustOwl Performance Testing"
.SH NAME
perf-tests.sh \- Performance testing and analysis for RustOwl
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B perf-tests.sh
[\fIOPTION\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBperf-tests.sh\fR script provides comprehensive performance testing and analysis for RustOwl. It measures various performance metrics of the current code state, including binary size, execution time, memory usage, symbol counts, and advanced analysis features.

The script is designed to help developers understand and validate the performance characteristics of their code with flexible metric selection, configurable test runs, and multiple output formats.

.SH OPTIONS
.SS Modes
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help information and exit
.TP
.B \-\-verify
Check the testing environment without running performance tests. Shows system information, tool availability, and enabled metrics.
.TP
.B \-\-prepare
Build the project without running tests. Ensures the binary is ready for testing.
.TP
.B \-\-test
Run performance tests (default mode). Measures selected metrics and displays results.

.SS Test Configuration
.TP
.B \-\-runs N
Number of test runs to perform (default: 3). Results are averaged across multiple runs for better accuracy.
.TP
.B \-\-warm
Skip cache clearing between runs. Tests performance with system caches intact.
.TP
.B \-\-cold
Clear caches between runs (default). Provides consistent measurements by eliminating cache effects.
.TP
.B \-\-force
Force rebuild even if binary exists. Ensures fresh compilation.

.SS Metrics Selection
By default, only size and time metrics are enabled. Specifying any metric flag disables defaults and enables only the requested metrics.
.TP
.B \-\-full
Enable all available metrics
.TP
.B \-\-size
Binary size analysis
.TP
.B \-\-time
Execution time measurement
.TP
.B \-\-symbols
Symbol count analysis (requires nm)
.TP
.B \-\-strip
Strip analysis showing debug symbol overhead
.TP
.B \-\-memory
Memory usage measurement
.TP
.B \-\-page-faults
Page fault counting
.TP
.B \-\-context-switches
Context switch measurement
.TP
.B \-\-static
Static analysis metrics
.TP
.B \-\-profile-memory
Memory profiling with valgrind (Linux only)
.TP
.B \-\-profile-cpu
CPU profiling recommendations

.SS Output Options
.TP
.B \-\-markdown FILE
Save results to markdown file instead of stdout
.TP
.B \-\-compare FILE
Compare current results with previous markdown results file

.SH TESTING MODES
.SS Default Mode (--test)
When run without mode arguments, performs performance testing:
.IP 1. 4
Builds the project using specific Rust toolchain
.IP 2. 4
Runs performance measurements for selected metrics
.IP 3. 4
Averages results across multiple runs
.IP 4. 4
Displays summary and optionally saves to markdown

.SS System Verification (--verify)
Check environment readiness:
.IP 1. 4
Verify required tools are available
.IP 2. 4
Show optional tool availability
.IP 3. 4
Display enabled metrics configuration
.IP 4. 4
.SH MEASUREMENTS
The script provides comprehensive analysis across multiple dimensions:

.SS Binary Analysis
.IP \(bu 4
Binary size measurement with human-readable formatting
.IP \(bu 4
Symbol count analysis (requires \fBnm\fR)
.IP \(bu 4
Strip analysis showing debug symbol overhead
.IP \(bu 4
Static analysis including binary entropy and dependencies

.SS Performance Metrics
.IP \(bu 4
Execution time (wall clock)
.IP \(bu 4
Peak memory usage (RSS)
.IP \(bu 4
Page faults (major/minor)
.IP \(bu 4
Context switches (voluntary/involuntary)

.SS Advanced Analysis
When optional tools are available:
.IP \(bu 4
Statistical benchmarking with confidence intervals (\fBhyperfine\fR)
.IP \(bu 4
Memory profiling with heap analysis (\fBvalgrind\fR on Linux)
.IP \(bu 4
CPU profiling recommendations for platform-specific tools

.SH BUILD SYSTEM
The script uses a specific Rust build configuration:

.SS Build Command
.B RUSTC_BOOTSTRAP=1 rustup run 1.86.0 cargo build --release

This ensures consistent compilation with Rust 1.86.0 stable compiler while enabling nightly features through RUSTC_BOOTSTRAP.

.SS Binary Location
Tests are performed directly on the binary in \fB./target/release/rustowl\fR without copying or moving files.

.SH CACHE MANAGEMENT
Performance measurements can be significantly affected by various system caches. The script provides cache management options:

.SS Cache Types
.IP \(bu 4
Filesystem caches (page cache) - Most significant impact
.IP \(bu 4
Rust incremental compilation cache
.IP \(bu 4
CPU caches (L1/L2/L3 and branch prediction)

.SS Cache Clearing Methods
.IP \(bu 4
macOS: \fBpurge\fR command (may require sudo)
.IP \(bu 4
Linux: \fB/proc/sys/vm/drop_caches\fR (requires sudo)
.IP \(bu 4
Rust: \fBcargo clean\fR for incremental cache

Use \fB--cold\fR (default) for consistent measurements or \fB--warm\fR for realistic cached performance.

.SH DEPENDENCIES
.SS Required Tools
.IP \(bu 4
\fBgit\fR - Version control operations
.IP \(bu 4
\fBcargo\fR - Rust build system
.IP \(bu 4
\fBbc\fR - Mathematical calculations
.IP \(bu 4
\fBrustup\fR - Rust toolchain management

.SS Optional Tools (Enhanced Features)
.IP \(bu 4
\fBhyperfine\fR - Statistical benchmarking
.IP \(bu 4
\fBvalgrind\fR - Memory profiling (Linux only)
.IP \(bu 4
\fBperf\fR - CPU profiling (Linux only)
.IP \(bu 4
\fBnm\fR - Symbol analysis
.IP \(bu 4
\fBinstruments\fR - CPU profiling (macOS with Xcode)

.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic Testing
.TP
.B perf-tests.sh --test
Run basic performance test with default metrics (size + time)
.TP
.B perf-tests.sh --verify
Check system readiness and tool availability
.TP
.B perf-tests.sh --test --full
Run comprehensive test with all available metrics

.SS Focused Testing
.TP
.B perf-tests.sh --test --memory --symbols --runs 5
Test memory usage and symbol counts with 5 runs for accuracy
.TP
.B perf-tests.sh --test --warm --time
Test execution time with warm caches (realistic performance)

.SS Output and Comparison
.TP
.B perf-tests.sh --test --markdown results.md
Save results to markdown file for documentation
.TP
.B perf-tests.sh --test --compare baseline.md
Compare current performance with previous results

.SH RESULT INTERPRETATION
.SS Normal Results
.IP \(bu 4
Consistent results across multiple runs
.IP \(bu 4
Reasonable execution times and memory usage
.IP \(bu 4
Expected symbol counts for binary size

.SS Investigate Further
.IP \(bu 4
Extreme performance variations between runs
.IP \(bu 4
Unusually high memory usage or execution time
.IP \(bu 4
Zero page faults (suggests measurement issues)

.SS Best Practices
.IP \(bu 4
Run \fB--verify\fR first to check environment
.IP \(bu 4
Use multiple runs for important measurements
.IP \(bu 4
Test on quiet systems with minimal background processes
.IP \(bu 4
Consider both cold and warm cache performance
.IP \(bu 4
Save results to markdown for tracking over time

.SH OUTPUT FORMATS
.SS Standard Output
Default format displays metrics to stdout with colored output and progress indicators.

.SS Markdown Output
Use \fB--markdown FILE\fR to generate structured markdown reports suitable for documentation and tracking.

.SS Comparison Output
Use \fB--compare FILE\fR to compare current results with previously saved markdown results, showing differences and changes.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error (missing tools, build failure, binary verification failure)

.SH FILES
.TP
.B ./target/release/rustowl
Main binary tested by the script
.TP
.B ./target/release/rustowlc
Compiler binary (also built but not directly tested)

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RUSTC_BOOTSTRAP
Set to 1 for stable compiler with nightly features
.TP
.B CARGO_TARGET_DIR
Cargo build directory (default: target/)
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
Disable colored output

.SH NOTES
This script is designed for development environments and focuses on testing the current code state without git-based comparisons. It prioritizes reproducibility and comprehensive metrics over raw speed.

For accurate performance measurements, consider running multiple iterations and using appropriate cache management options based on your testing goals.

